title: The Strikers Lab Gym (Muay Thai, Kickboxing & Boxing)
name: Antonio Logronio
text: In the already competitive landscape of gyms in Western Sydney let alone combat sports/fight gyms, this is definitely a gym I highly recommend... The gym owner (coach Franz) while firm, is also very fair... He is a retired ex kick boxing/muay thai champion and runs a very professional gym which even offers kids classes, wrestling n boxing classes for all skill n fitness levels! 1 of the rare fight gyms wid elephant mats and a proper ring, body shields, shin guards n overall well kept equipment!

title: The Strikers Lab Gym (Muay Thai, Kickboxing & Boxing)
name: Tristan Uru
text:
If you're looking for a top-tier gym that combines cutting-edge equipment with expert coaching, look no further than Strikers Lab. From the moment you walk in, you can tell this place is designed for serious athletes. The quality of the equipment is second to none—whether you’re hitting the bags, working on footwork, or using the strength and conditioning tools, everything is high-end and meticulously maintained.

What truly sets Strikers Lab apart, however, is Coach Franz. His expertise, passion, and personalized coaching style make a huge difference. He’s not just a coach; he's a mentor who knows how to push you to reach your potential while ensuring that every movement is precise and effective. Whether you're a beginner or a seasoned pro, Coach Franz will meet you where you're at and help you improve.

The atmosphere at Strikers Lab is also incredibly motivating. It’s clear that everyone here is serious about their training, and the community vibe makes it even more rewarding. If you’re serious about leveling up your fitness or combat skills, Strikers Lab is hands down one of the best places you can train. Highly recommend!

title: The Strikers Lab Gym (Muay Thai, Kickboxing & Boxing)
name: Happy GoLucky
text:
BEWARE NEW JOINERS! Prices are cheap for a reason. This review is from a customer’s standpoint who came in for a trial.

There is really only one trainer/owner here who is always on his phone. The instructor/owner has a very bad attitude. Came in for a trial, no introduction, no interest in what my fighting experience has been or anything.

Had been to the intermediate and beginner class, there is not much difference at all. Only one ring which doesn’t get used.

If all you want to do is some combos which you cannot use in a real fight, low grade equipment (thai pads) and an instructor who is always on their phone, then yes join this place.

title: The Strikers Lab Gym (Muay Thai, Kickboxing & Boxing)

text: Best gym ever I recommend going coach Franz knows his tuff

title: The Strikers Lab Gym (Muay Thai, Kickboxing & Boxing)
name: Dominic Ngen
text:
I’ve made a review before but it wasn’t a serious review but more of a humorous review, Here is my honest and serious thought about the Strikers Lab Gym.

The coach Franz "Dirty" Sanchez was able to turn me, a MMA fighter that primarily focuses on Judo, Wrestling, Brazilian Jiujutsu, Japanese Jiujutsu, Kempo Jiujutsu, Gojo Ryu Karate and Capoeira, into an even better MMA fighter by teaching me well with Muay Thai, Boxing and Kickboxing.

I find that The Strikers Lab Gym is one of the best Martial Art Gyms in Sydney and highly recommended if it is your first time doing Martial Arts or if your experienced and need a place to train.

100/10 Highly Recommended

title: The Strikers Lab Gym (Muay Thai, Kickboxing & Boxing)
name: Ewan Rogers
text: The Strikers Lab gym is one of the most welcoming communities I have encountered. From the kind natured people who train there, to the elite coach Franz, the gym is as a whole one you will be sure to enjoy. Franz’s national champion title status speaks for itself. Franz tries to get the best out of you and will do his best to help you achieve your goals. His people skills allows for great communication and his empathetic nature creates a comfortable environment. His depth of knowledge is rare to encounter and should not be overlooked. If you don’t believe this review, get to the gym try it for yourself.

title: The Strikers Lab Gym (Muay Thai, Kickboxing & Boxing)
name: OfficialStephenKovacs
text: I joined The Strikers Lab after years of contemplating. I had been in to a few gyms and never felt welcomed or like they had time to even talk to you unless you were part of the “fight team”. This place is different! Immediately welcome and the vibe is awesome. There are no egos here and just a passion to learn and be better every day. High quality training and everyone is treated equally so if you pick The Strikers Lab to train at you’ll feel right at home.

title: The Strikers Lab Gym (Muay Thai, Kickboxing & Boxing)
name: Jennifer Nguyen
text: I joined The Strikers Lab Gym this year, and training with Franz has been a game changer. He’s created such a friendly and welcoming environment, but he’s also firm and pushes you to reach your full potential.

title: The Strikers Lab Gym (Muay Thai, Kickboxing & Boxing)
name: David Mansour
text:
One of the best  Muay Thai gyms in Sydney.

You get
-Affordable payment options.
-Amazing training for beginners and fighters
-Feedback with incredible attention to detail to improve your skills.
-A great community of people from all different ages and backgrounds.
-First 3 lessons free.

If you ever wanted to try Muay Thai, give Strikers Lab a go. You can't go wrong.

title: The Strikers Lab Gym (Muay Thai, Kickboxing & Boxing)
name: Sara Overton
text: I Love this gym , I'm so glad I found it I have been to multiple Muay Thai gyms in the years and can say this one has a great vibe , The trainer Franz is very respectful and has a real eye for detail, he makes the effort for all his students not just the fighters , he is always helping correct form and will even pair you up with someone that is your level to ensure you get the most of your class. You will also find often other gyms coming to spar here too so you will get a good mix of new styles to help perfect your sparring skills. This gym was recently updated and is exceptionally clean and quality equipment. It's obvious Franz puts alot of pride into his gym and he even holds in house family events for members , I have never seen this happen in other gyms.  There is one thing for sure you will progress fast here , Franz is a professional fighter with great teaching skills . I will add the membership price is also very competitive. If your looking for a Muay Thai gym this is the spot .

title: The Strikers Lab Gym (Muay Thai, Kickboxing & Boxing)
name: Robert Bordignon
text: Great gym with an experienced attentive head coach in Franz. As someone who came to the gym with no prior experience head coach Franz has always ensured his coaching is aimed at helping students learn and better their martial arts. His hands on approach is tailored to each students strengths and/or weaknesses taking time to really ensure everyone that attends the gym classes improves as fighters. The Gym is new, clean and has great quality equipment to borrow. Franz creates a friendly welcoming environment but also commands discipline and punctuality as a coach so that his students can experience the best results to grow into fighters that can achieve their goals and one day step in the ring.

title: The Strikers Lab Gym (Muay Thai, Kickboxing & Boxing)
name: Viniccius Marangoni
text: Great gym for people who want to learn Muay Thai or Boxing, from beginners to advanced. Coach Franz has many years of experience. I improved so much since I joined the team.

title: The Strikers Lab Gym (Muay Thai, Kickboxing & Boxing)
name: Christian Gamallo
text: A place for all levels whether your curious to try or aiming to further your skills. TSL and Coach Sanchez really care about nurturing and honing in on your muay thai journey sharing wisdom from a decorated professional career. A great place for learning and loving muay thai and boxing for everyone!

title: The Strikers Lab Gym (Muay Thai, Kickboxing & Boxing)

Great gym, highly recommended for martial arts lovers or just for fitness.
The gym is always clean, Franz the head coach is always there to help you improve your skills. Absolutely love it!

title: The Strikers Lab Gym (Muay Thai, Kickboxing & Boxing)
name: michael reed
text: When I changed jobs I could no longer attend classes as I had gone to night shift. Explained this to Franz,and instead of wishing me well and sending me on my way,he accommodated me and got me doing different times to suit my situation.  I find the workouts exhausting and tough and Franz an amazing teacher. Some people can teach and some can't. Franz is the former. His gym is clean and tidy. The gear is top notch. HIGHLY recommend coming down, and EMBRACE THE PAIN ,LOL, yes it's GOING TO BE TOUGH,but with Franz, you'll get this done. You'll feel confident and strong in your Daily life....promise.⚡️⚡️⚡️🎵🎵🎵
